-- Court orders seizure of 245 million euros at UniCredit: sources
-- 
-- Tue Oct 18, 2011 1:49pm EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2011/10/18/us-unicredit-probe-idUSTRE79H5I420111018

 

 MILAN  (Reuters) - A Milan court has ordered the seizure of 245 million euros ($336.5 million) at UniCredit, Italy's biggest bank by assets, and put its former CEO Alessandro Profumo under investigation for alleged tax fraud, judicial sources said on Tuesday. 
 UniCredit was not available for comment. (Reporting By Manuela D'Alessandro)